This paper is about training and inference for Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the resilience of CNNs to compression schemes, which falls under the category of machine learning and optimization. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of back-propagation, which is a common optimization technique used in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely category. The paper also discusses the use of existing neural network architectures, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. Finally, the paper discusses the resource usage of GPU and memory, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category as well.
